@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@userId = 7a26f2f7-2d21-4c56-954f-56449b8998e0
@courseId = 6680832f-e10b-42f7-821c-503fbc89f00b

### ================================================================
###                    1. AUTH CONTROLLER
### ================================================================

### 1.1 Registrar um novo usuário (Sign Up)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "matheus79",
  "email": "matheus79@email.com",
  "password": "password79",
  "fullName": "Matheus Torres",
  "phoneNumber": "11999999999",
  "cpf": "12345678903",
  "imageUrl": "http://image.com/matheus.png"
}

### 1.2 Registrar segundo usuário (aluno para testes)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "aluno01",
  "email": "aluno01@email.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "fullName": "Aluno Teste",
  "phoneNumber": "11977777777",
  "cpf": "98765432100",
  "imageUrl": "http://image.com/aluno.png"
}

### 1.3 Autenticar usuário (Login)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "matheus79",
  "password": "password79"
}


### ================================================================
###                2. INSTRUCTOR CONTROLLER
### ================================================================

### 2.1 Registrar usuário como instrutor
POST {{baseUrl}}/instructors/subscription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}


### ================================================================
###                    3. USER CONTROLLER
### ================================================================

### 3.1 Buscar todos os usuários (Paginado e Ordenado)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=0&size=5&sort=userId,asc
Accept: application/json

### 3.2 Buscar todos os usuários (Com Filtro Specification)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?userType=STUDENT&userStatus=ACTIVE
Accept: application/json

### 3.3 Buscar todos os usuários por tipo INSTRUCTOR
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?userType=INSTRUCTOR
Accept: application/json

### 3.4 Buscar todos os usuários de um curso específico (courseId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?courseId={{courseId}}
Accept: application/json

### 3.5 Buscar usuário por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### 3.6 Atualizar dados básicos do usuário
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Matheus Torres",
  "phoneNumber": "11988888888",
  "cpf": "12345678901"
}

### 3.7 Atualizar senha do usuário
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "password123",
  "password": "newpassword123"
}

### 3.8 Atualizar imagem do usuário
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/image
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "imageUrl": "http://image.com/matheus_new_profile.png"
}

### 3.9 Deletar usuário
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}


### ================================================================
###              4. USER-COURSE CONTROLLER (OpenFeign)
### ================================================================

### 4.1 Listar cursos de um usuário (via Feign -> Course Service)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/courses?page=0&size=10&sort=courseId,asc
Accept: application/json

### 4.2 Inscrever usuário em um curso (via AuthUser Service)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/courses/subscription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}"
}


### ================================================================
###              5. COURSE-USER CONTROLLER (OpenFeign)
### ================================================================

### 5.1 Listar usuários de um curso (via Feign -> AuthUser Service)
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/{{courseId}}/users?page=0&size=10&sort=userId,asc
Accept: application/json

### 5.2 Inscrever usuário em um curso (via Course Service -> AuthUser)
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses/{{courseId}}/users/subscription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}


### ================================================================
###              6. REFRESH SCOPE CONTROLLER (Tests)
### ================================================================

### 6.1 Testar @RefreshScope (configurações externas)
GET {{baseUrl}}/refreshscope

